cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new framework that improves segmentation quality, which involves machine learning techniques such as feature fusion. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in computer vision, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a segmentation benchmark, which is a common evaluation metric in multimedia research, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
